when you zone the new zone is suppose to be loaded up into your ram and the old zone erased ect ect each time you zone but for some reason windows doesn't want to erase your old zones so they stay loaded on there and it keeps buidling up until you Run out of RAM  eventually on my freinds it would get so bad that it would just freeze or i'd move stop for 5 mins move again stop ect ect..<br />
<br />
<br />
I figured this out when running a memory manager program and while playing EQ i went from 100ram free to 2mb free after 5 zones and i had to log for video choppyness<br />
<br />
When It happens a lot on the newer windows models after 98   currently i'm using 98 and having no problem.<br />
